Common.Brochures.Common.BrochureName: 2020 - Brochure - 609 E. Atlantic Ave - Atlantic Crossing.pdf

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Intersection "Main & Main" Atlantic Avenue and Federal Hwy

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: A green and walkable destination, it’s a natural extension of Downtown Delray’s authentic and eclectic charm, gracefully weaving together generous public spaces, lively streetscapes, and distinctive design to bring four city blocks to life. Best-in-class companies, like anchor tenant Merrill Lynch, will find Atlantic Crossing – Downtown Delray’s first new Class A office space – an ideal business address. With large floorplates, green features and a unique setting, Atlantic Crossing is convenient, walkable and a perfect blend of business and pleasure.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Atlantic Crossing brings added dimensions to Delray Beach’s acclaimed Atlantic Avenue with new choices for living, working, shopping and enjoying city life.

Common.Brochures.Common.BrochureName: 14000 S Miliray Trail - Delray Prodessional center (2).pdf

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: CBRE is pleased to offer The Delray Professional Center for lease. This two-story glass office building with an underground parking garage. Located in South Palm Beach County, featuring a marble lobby with giant art adorning the walls and suites ranging from 1,600 SF to 5,300 SF with in-suite private restrooms. The entire building was remodeled in 2003. Tenants enjoy the convenient location between Lake Ida and Atlantic Blvd. along S. Military Trail. The property is situated between 4 miles from the Turnpike and just 3 miles from I-95. Within walking distance to the US Post Office, shops, medical facilitates, restaurants, and much more.
